FBIS4-41633 "drsov123_f_94018" FBIS-SOV-94-123 Daily Report 26 Jun 1994 National Affairs Kravchuk Says 450,000 Serving in Army Kravchuk Says 450,000 Serving in Army LD2606185694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1530 GMT 26 Jun 94 LD2606185694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service Russian BFN [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondents Viktor Demidenko and Mikhail Melnik] [Excerpt] Kiev, 26 Jun -- [Passage omitted] "At the present stage, Ukraine's Armed Forces are being organized and developed in accordance with our state's military doctrine. There are currently 450,000 servicemen in the Army," Leonid Kravchuk said. "I do not think this number is final. The question of the organization of the Army and its armament is under constant study and is the focus of the attention of state bodies. The possibility of some Army subunits switching to service on a professional basis is being examined." [passage omitted]
